  "description": [
    "Vol 62 No 27 3 Major Changes In Navy Proficiency Pay Program Three major changes have been noted in the Navys pro ficiencv pav program for fiscal 1963 which went into effect on Sunday 1 July The new program savs Naw Times w hich divides navymen into three groups instead of the present two so far as propay is concerned has changes which will give automatic P2 pay to about 2500 men in 33 ultracritical specialties added 17 new NECs to the automatic P1 and opportunity for P2 list and re quires that a man drawing P1 pay be drawing the extra 3O a month only three months instead of the present six to become eligible for P2 pay With the exception of men in the 33 ultracritical specialties all the rest of the ratings and NECs which got P1 automatic ally last summer and who alone were eligible to compete for P2 pay stay in the same situation this coming fiscal year The one exception is NEC 9972 which is being phased out UltraCritical NECs Concerning the 2500 sailors in 33 ultracritical NECs not only do they get the P1 pay auto matically but all who have been drawing"
